%global packname  gds
%global packver   0.1.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.1.0
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Descriptive Statistics of Grouped Data

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Contains a function called gds() which accepts three input parameters like
lower limits, upper limits and the frequencies of the corresponding
classes. The gds() function calculate and return the values of mean
('gmean'), median ('gmedian'), mode ('gmode'), variance ('gvar'), standard
deviation ('gstdev'), coefficient of variance ('gcv'), quartiles ('gq1',
'gq2', 'gq3'), inter-quartile range ('gIQR'), skewness ('g1'), and
kurtosis ('g2') which facilitate effective data analysis. For skewness and
kurtosis calculations we use moments.

